            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Pour Artemis.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>For Artemis.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Per Artemis.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>لأجل أرتميس</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Found in a <foreign rend="italic">thesauron</foreign> inside the pronaos of the 2nd-phase Artemision. About the discovery, see a page of Pernier's 
                    excavation note-book now published by <bibl><ptr target="#bartolini2014a"/></bibl>; this sherd was part of the 'treasure of Benghazi', which has been stolen in 2011 at the National 
                    Commercial Bank at Benghazi, as shown by <bibl><ptr target="#ensoli2012"/></bibl>.</p>
                <p/>
	<p/>
